<br>
In my opinion, EQAnnounce corrects one problem that I have with Everquest...lost lines of text regarding the status of buffs that I have placed on my party.  As a cleric, I keep a lot of the text settings to &quot;ON&quot;, ie others hits, so that I can keep a good feel of the flow of battle.  Often, however, my scanning ability is limited to damage, I often miss when buffs fade.  A verbal announcement would help overcome my problem without changing gameplay.  I realize that one solution is to self-buff at the same time, but mana does not always allow for self-buffing.<br>
<br>
The use of timers for EQ has been going on since beta, and probably won't stop.  The fundamental difference here is that instead of setting a physical timer, the log file is parsed (obviously not changing game play as game events are logged AFTER they occur) and updated to allow for an audible timer.<br>
<br>
I hope that this product is approved for use, it would enhance gameplay.<br>
<br>
John Lane <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF33>- </font><a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/beqannounce>EQAnnounce</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5>General</a> <font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/beqannounce">EQAnnounce Message Boards</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
